From 1e6dc9c0e5040bcde176ecc58ed0e346af3edb9d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: RivonClaw CI <ci@rivonclaw.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 18:15:30 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] vendor(openclaw): dedupe directly sent block media

Why:
- Temporary backport of the upstream reply-media dedupe fixes in openclaw/openclaw@9922da3965 and openclaw/openclaw@41000143a1.
- RivonClaw's pinned vendor can deliver block attachments immediately and then reconstruct the same media in the final payload, duplicating the first attachment.
- Track only successfully delivered text and media evidence so failed sends still remain eligible for final delivery.

Removal:
- Delete this temporary patch after upgrading to an OpenClaw revision containing both 9922da3965 and 41000143a1.

Tests:
- apps/desktop/src/channels/vendor-direct-block-media-dedupe.sentinel.test.ts
- src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-payloads.test.ts
- src/auto-reply/reply/reply-delivery.test.ts
